<P>
TRADITIONAL PARDONS GRANTED TO IRANIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Iran's spiritual leader, the Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, on Sunday pardoned or cut 
the sentences of 2,389 prisoners, Tehran Television reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The television did not give the length of sentences being served or the 
severity of the crimes for which pardons were issued. 
</P>
<P>
 The pardons were granted, in accordance with tradition, to mark the 
anniversary in the Islamic religion of the revelation of God's mission to the 
Prophet Mohammed. 
</P>
