MEDIA ACCESS WORKSHOP FEATURES KCAL ANCHOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Veteran news anchor Pat Harvey of KCAL-TV will be the keynote speaker Jan. 22 
at a workshop titled "How to Get Your News in the Newspaper and on the Air" 
presented by United Media Access Panel (UMAP). 
</P>
<P>
 Funded by the Ford Foundation, the free session, fifth in a series of nine 
workshops, will be held from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the Watts Health Center, 
10300 S. Compton Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics to be covered include how to prepare a news release, how to find key 
contacts at radio, TV and newspapers and tips on establishing relationships and 
working with the media. 
</P>
<P>
 Among media panelists participating are Angela Johnson of the L.A. Watts 
Times, Luis Patino and Arte Shammamian of KCAL-TV, Dean Takahashi of the Los 
Angeles Times Orange County edition, Victoria Easley of KFWB and Ron Brewington 
of Sheridan Broadcasting Network. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Song of the Korean American Grocers Assn. of California and Sandra Serano 
Sewell of Centro de Ninos will be among community representatives sharing tips 
and success stories. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 461-1506. 
