<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: GUIDEBOOK FOR OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new guidebook that outlines nature walks and other activities planned this 
winter in the Santa Monica Mountains National Recreation Area is available free 
of charge from the National Park Service. 
</P>
<P>
 The booklet allows visitors to plan activities that are designed specifically 
for children of various ages, singles, seniors and birders.For instance, the 
"Babes in the Woods" outing on Sunday invites parents with stroller-age 
children to join them on a walk around the Upper Franklin Canyon Reservoir. 
"Learn how to introduce the natural world to your child," the booklet says. 
</P>
<P>
 A more strenuous hike along the Backbone Trail has master trail builder Ron 
Webster leading a 10-mile trek. The booklet also includes details on "Fungus 
Forays," wildflower walks and hikes under the full moon. 
</P>
<P>
 To receive a copy of the guidebook, write Santa Monica Mountains National 
Recreation Area, 30401 Agoura Road, Suite 100, Agoura Hills 91301, or call 
(818) 597-9192. JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
