<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; UC EXTENSION KNOWS WHEN TO SOW, REAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Want to know when to plant cucumbers or what type of tomatoes grow best in 
your area? 
</P>
<P>
 The University of California Cooperative Extension has the answers to these 
and other gardening questions.The department maintains an extensive list of 
pamphlets, books and other publications on a variety of topics. 
</P>
<P>
 "The main purpose is to disseminate information to farmers and local 
residents," said William N. Miller, who works in the information services 
division of the Department of Agriculture. 
</P>
<P>
 The extension service also has a program to help low-income residents improve 
their nutrition and stretch their budgets through careful shopping and oversees 
the local 4-H program. 
</P>
<P>
 Part of the UC system, the cooperative extension is located at the Orange 
County Fairgrounds. For more information, call (714) 708-1606. DANIELLE A. 
FOUQUETTE 
</P>
