<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 8 SCHOOL PRINCIPALS TO CHANGE POSITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eight elementary school principals in the Saddleback Valley Unified School 
District will be changing positions for the 1994-95 year, district officials 
announced last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Burt, principal of Gates Elementary in Lake Forest, has been named 
principal of the new Robinson Ranch Elementary School, which is scheduled to 
open in September.Beginning next month, he will serve in an interim position as 
principal of Trabuco Elementary in Trabuco Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Hamilton, the district's personnel services director, will take over as 
principal at Gates Elementary. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Herdman at Trabuco Mesa Elementary in Rancho Santa Margarita and Chuck 
Prince at De Portola Elementary in Mission Viejo will swap their principal 
posts. 
</P>
<P>
 David Whitcher, principal at Olivewood Elementary in Lake Forest, will take 
the head position at Linda Vista Elementary in Mission Viejo, replacing 
principal Kathy Dick, who has been assigned to Aliso Elementary in Lake Forest. 
</P>
<P>
 Aliso's principal, Mike Delaney, will move to Del Cerro Elementary and La 
Tierra Elementary in Mission Viejo, replacing principal Suzanne Westmoreland, 
who is relocating to Olivewood Elementary. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials also announced that in September, 1995, Carole 
McLelland-Wong, principal of Del Lago Elementary in Mission Viejo, will become 
principal of the school now under construction in Foothill Ranch, which is 
scheduled to open in September of that year. RICHARD CORE 
</P>
