<HEADLINE>
<P>
SONNY BONO PLANS TO RUN FOR CONGRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sonny Bono, the former mayor of the desert resort, said he will announce his 
candidacy for Congress this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Bono said he will announce Tuesday that he is seeking the Republican 
nomination for the seat of Rep. Al McCandless."This is the best job for me," 
Bono said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 McCandless, a Republican, declared last week that he will not seek a seventh 
term. 
</P>
<P>
 Bono, 58, made his comments during a reception at his home for actress Sophia 
Loren, who was honored during the Palm Springs International Film Festival. 
Bono helped found the festival. 
</P>
<P>
 Bono ran for the Republican nomination to the U.S. Senate in 1992 but lost the 
primary to conservative commentator Bruce Herschensohn, who was defeated by 
Democrat Barbara Boxer. 
</P>
