<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: COME ON, JUST GIVE US A HINT . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Martha Groves 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cold War has been declared over, but Lawrence Livermore National 
Laboratory apparently still believes in the wartime adage, "Loose lips sink 
ships." 
</P>
<P>
 The lab, one of two national centers for design of nuclear weapons, late last 
year received a prestigious award from the CIA and the National Security 
Agency. The Intelligence Community Seal Medallion, presented to the "Project 
Woodpecker" team, is on display at the lab, east of San Francisco in Livermore. 
</P>
<P>
 Problem is, Lawrence Livermore can't say what it's for. As one lab engineer 
lamented: "We're trying to get it declassified so we can talk about it." Martha 
Groves 
</P>
</TEXT>
