<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INTERNATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 China Posts Biggest Trade Deficit Since 1985: China customs data show its 
trade deficit in 1993 was $12.18 billion, the biggest since a $14.9-billion 
trade gap in 1985 and its first deficit since 1989. Total trade jumped 18% to a 
record $195.7 billion, but most of that came from a 29% increase in imports to 
$103.9 billion that swamped an 8% gain in exports. While the gap increases 
pressure on Beijing to boost exports and control imports, the United States and 
other countries are clamoring for more access to China's markets. 
</P>
