88 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUSTRALIAN INSURERS CALL BRUSH FIRE LOSSES MODERATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Bloomberg Business News 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Australian insurers say property losses to date from savage brush fires in and 
around Sydney are moderate compared with losses from the nation's past natural 
disasters. 
</P>
<P>
 The Insurance Council of Australia, in a preliminary estimate, said it expects 
losses to total about $68.5 million, equally divided between residential and 
commercial property. 
</P>
<P>
 About 135 fires were reported still burning in New South Wales state this 
morning, but cooler, moister weather today has eased conditions that fanned the 
flames in recent days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
