BRIEFLY: INTERNATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Major Hikes Estimate of Growth: British Prime Minister John Major said his 
government estimated the country's economy would grow perhaps as much as 3% 
this year.That compares with a 2.5% increase estimated last November. Major 
told a BBC interviewer there could be a large decrease in unemployment in 1994 
and he expects inflation to remain in the range of 1% to 4% until mid-1997. In 
1993, Britain emerged from a 2 1/2-year recession and is expected to have the 
highest growth rate in the European Union in 1994. However, the jobless rate 
remains at 10%. 
</P>
