<P>
BRIEFLY: ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Economists Predict Vigorous Growth: The U.S. economy will grow by 3% this 
year, adjusted for inflation, said a group of 51 economists polled by Blue Chip 
Economic Indicators. If they are correct, it would be the economy's strongest 
performance since the 3.9% expansion in 1988. Momentum from the growth in the 
final quarter of 1993 -- now placed at an annual rate of 4.2% -- will carry 
over into the new year, the panel predicted, with strength in housing, autos 
and other consumer durables persisting into 1994. 
</P>
