BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gasoline Prices Drop: The average price of gasoline, including all grades and 
taxes, was $1.0949 a gallon last week, down 1.29 cents from the previous 
survey, industry analyst Trilby Lundberg of the Lundberg Survey said.The trend 
of price drops is slowing and has bottomed out in some areas, Lundberg said. An 
upward price turnaround has also made a showing in Midwestern and Gulf Coast 
states, she said. At self-serve pumps, average prices per gallon were: regular 
unleaded $1.021; mid-grade unleaded $1.1389; premium unleaded $1.2198; regular 
leaded $1.0369. 
</P>
