BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oil Spill Charges Filed Too Late, Judge Rules: Allegations that Unocal Corp. 
covered up spills at its Guadalupe oil field cannot be pursued because 
prosecutors missed the statute of limitations by two days, San Luis Obispo 
County Municipal Judge James D. Ream said. However, he said there was 
"substantial evidence" that "Unocal and its employees actively engaged in a 
course of conduct which included not only failing to disclose the leaks, but 
(taking) steps to prevent the leaks from coming to the attention of the 
public."Prosecutors filed 28 misdemeanor charges alleging that Unocal and six 
employees failed to report more than 100 leaks since 1985. Los Angeles-based 
Unocal says it alerted authorities immediately after the problem was discovered 
in February, 1990. 
</P>
