<TEXT>
<P>
 Government Acts to Revive Property Market: Low-interest loans will be offered 
to real estate developers buying land in Tokyo, Osaka and Nagoya, the Nihon 
Keizai newspaper reported. The government will also provide more funding to 
public housing projects to make it easier for individuals to buy a home, it 
said. Japanese business leaders are asking for a cut in personal income taxes 
to stimulate personal spending. 
