<TEXT>
<P>
 Retail Sales Soar: The figure grew by an adjusted 2.1% in November, the 
largest increase in two years, confirming economists' belief that Australia's 
three-year economic slump may be at an end.The retail sales growth was more 
than 10 times the 0.2% gain analysts had forecast. "These are wonderful numbers 
for the economy," said Chris Caton, chief economist with Bankers Trust 
Australia. "Consumers are spending again, labor market indicators are 
favorable, business sector confidence is recovering, exports are still strong. 
We're on our way again." 
